s.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Illinois</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Washington DC</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">US states</category><media:content url="https://static01.nyt.com/images/2026/04/30/multimedia/WAYMO-politics-02-pvqz/WAYMO-politics-02-pvqz-videoSixteenByNineJumbo1600.jpg" medium="image"><media:credit>Manuel Orbegozo for The New York Times</media:credit></media:content></item><item><title>The Cloud Has Sound: The Unrelenting and Unseen Cost of A.I. Data Centers</title><link>https://www.nytimes.com/2026/06/17/us/data-centers-noise-pollution.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss</link><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.nytimes.com/2026/06/17/us/data-centers-noise-pollution.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss</guid><atom:link rel="standout" href="https://www.nytimes.com/2026/06/17/us/data-centers-noise-pollution.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss" /><description>As tech giants rush to build infrastructure, some residents who live near data centers say a constant low-frequency vibration is ruining their health and homes.</description><dc:creator>Adeel Hassan</dc:creator><pubDate>Wed, 17 Jun 2026 09:00:27 GMT</pubDate><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Data center</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Noise</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Zoning</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Regulation and Deregulation</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Lawsuits</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Artificial intelligence</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Construction</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Real Estate</category><category domain="htt